# phase1/.dockerignore — IN-030 v118 ROOT FIX (Teammate 8)
# =========================================================================
# The root .dockerignore covers the WHOLE repo context, but the
# phase1 Dockerfile (phase1/docker/Dockerfile.mlflow) builds with
# ``context: ./phase1`` (the phase1 directory) — meaning this file
# applies whenever someone builds the MLflow image or any phase1-
# specific image directly from the phase1/ directory.
#
# Without this file, ``docker build -t drugos-mlflow ./phase1`` sends
# ``raw_data/`` (10+ GB of ChEMBL, DrugBank, UniProt, STRING, DisGeNET,
# OMIM, PubChem downloads), ``processed_data/`` (CSVs with real drug-
# disease associations), ``tests/``, ``__pycache__``, ``.venv``, and
# ``phase1.db`` to the daemon as the build context — a 10+ GB tarball
# that exhausts Docker daemon memory and risks shipping real biomedical
# data + potentially-PHI annotations to a registry.
#
# This file mirrors the patterns from the root .dockerignore but adds
# phase1-specific patterns (raw_data, processed_data, the local SQLite
# dev DB, Airflow logs).
#
# The phase1 Dockerfiles only COPY:
#   - phase1/requirements.txt
#   - phase1/dags/
#   - phase1/pipelines/
#   - phase1/database/
#   - phase1/service/
#   - phase1/contracts/
#   - phase1/docker/ (entrypoint scripts)
# So everything else here is excluded from the build context.

# Raw biomedical data downloads — NEVER in the build context.
# These can be 10+ GB total (ChEMBL ~3GB, DrugBank ~500MB, UniProt ~2GB,
# STRING ~3GB, DisGeNET ~500MB, OMIM ~100MB, PubChem ~1GB).
# They are downloaded by the Airflow ETL pipelines at RUNTIME, not at
# BUILD time. Shipping them in the image would:
#   1. Make the image 10+ GB.
#   2. Pin the data to a specific snapshot (no auto-refresh).
#   3. Risk shipping potentially-licensed data to a public registry
#      (ChEMBL CC BY-SA, DrugBank requires license, etc.).
raw_data
raw_data/**

# Processed data — NEVER in the build context.
# These are the CSVs produced by the ETL pipelines (drugbank_indications.csv,
# chembl_activities.csv, etc.). They are regenerated on every ETL run.
# Shipping them in the image pins the KG to a specific data vintage.
processed_data
processed_data/**

# Local SQLite DB — NEVER in production images.
# ``phase1.db`` is a dev convenience for running the phase1 service
# without a Postgres instance. Shipping it to a registry leaks any
# locally-loaded drug-disease associations.
*.db
*.db-journal
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
phase1.db

# Python bytecode caches — never needed inside a container.
__pycache__
__pycache__/**
**/__pycache__
**/__pycache__/**
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# Virtual envs — NEVER in the build context.
.venv
.venv/**
venv
venv/**

# Tests and test artifacts — NEVER in production images.
tests
tests/**
*.test.py
*_test.py

# Airflow logs and DB — NEVER in the build context.
# ``airflow.db`` is the LocalExecutor metadata DB. ``logs/`` contains
# task instance logs which may include sensitive DAG parameters.
airflow.db
airflow.db-journal
logs
logs/**

# IDE / editor config — never needed inside a container.
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store

# Version control — never needed inside a container.
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Local env files — NEVER in production images.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.env

# Tooling configs that are not needed at build time.
.pytest_cache
.mypy_cache
.ruff_cache
.coverage
htmlcov
